  "A factory produces light bulbs with an average lifetime of 1,200 hours. A quality inspector tests 5 bulbs and finds an average lifetime of 1,050 hours. She then tests 5,000 bulbs and finds an average of 1,195 hours. Which average is more likely to be close to the true mean, and why?": "",
